<p><lb/>My Cosen Marsh the older <lb/>sent me a kind letter to <lb/>signify <choice><orig>y<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></orig><reg>that</reg></choice> after my clyster <lb/>&amp; blood letting she was well <lb/>for 4 days &amp; then payned as <lb/>before in her hed &amp; arme <lb/>so greevously betwixt 4 &amp; 5 <lb/>p m <choice><orig><choice><sic>cōnoly</sic><corr>cōmonly</corr></choice></orig><reg>commonly</reg></choice> Sept 14. <choice><orig>♀</orig><reg type="gloss">Friday</reg></choice> <lb/>h. 5. 30 p m 1627 <lb/>she sent to <rs type="address" xml:id="address1">Cambridg</rs> to M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> <lb/>Crane he gave her a pil<subst><del type="over">s</del><add place="over">l</add></subst> <lb/>&amp; also a clyster</p>
<p><lb/>had the horse leaches &amp; they were <gap extent="2" unit="chars" reason="blotDel"/> naught.</p>
<p><lb/>took my pils &amp; Dyet drink &amp; <lb/>did well for the tyme</p>
<p><lb/>her Daughter fond <choice><sic>mtch</sic><corr>mutch</corr></choice> good <lb/>by her playster Desyreth <lb/>a nother &amp; a recept of it</p>
</div>
